<!DOCTYPE chapter SYSTEM "cruise_help.dtd">
<chapter title="Mailhost information">
  <p>In order to allow <cref topic="dev_notifications">email notifications</cref>, we need to tell Go information about your mailhost.</p>
  <bullets>
    <item>Click on the <cref topic="administration_page">Administration</cref> tab</item>
    <img src="resources/images/cruise/topnav_admin.png" />
    <item>Click on the 'Server Configuration' sub-tab</item>
    <item>Add your mailhost information (with username and password as required)</item>
    <img src="resources/images/cruise/admin/mailhost_info/3_add_mailhost_info.png" />
    <item>Add an Administrator email address (this account will be emailed if the Go server is <cref topic="admin_out_of_disk_space">running out of disk space</cref>)</item>
    <item>Click 'Send test email' to verify the configuration is working correctly</item>
    <item>Click 'Save' when you're sure it's working.</item>
  </bullets>
</chapter>
